        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "General Agent Benchmarks"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Benchmarks give agents a score the same way tests give code a coverage number \u2014 a controlled, reproducible measure of capability that tracks progress and surfaces regressions. For agents the challenge is harder than for static models: the agent acts in an environment, the environment changes after each action, and many benchmarks require 10\u201330 sequential steps to complete a single task. This document surveys the four most-used general-purpose agent benchmarks and shows how to run and interpret each one."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Landscape Overview"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "General Agent Benchmarks Overview"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The four benchmarks cover complementary evaluation axes: web UI navigation (WebArena), multi-step question answering (GAIA), breadth across eight heterogeneous environments (AgentBench), and tool-calling accuracy under realistic API schemas (tau-bench). No single benchmark is sufficient \u2014 a model can score highly on GAIA while performing poorly on WebArena because they reward different skills."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "WebArena"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "WebArena provides five self-hosted web applications \u2014 an e-commerce store, a code repository, a content management system, a map, and a social platform \u2014 and 812 tasks that require navigating them using browser actions. Observations are accessibility trees (not pixel screenshots), making the benchmark model-accessible without vision."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Install: pip install browsergym playwright\n# playwright install chromium\nfrom browsergym.envs.webarena import WebArenaEnv\nimport anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\ndef run_webarena_task(task_id: int) -> dict:\n    env = WebArenaEnv(task_id=task_id, headless=True)\n    obs, info = env.reset()\n    done = False\n    steps = 0\n    max_steps = 30\n\n    while not done and steps < max_steps:\n        # obs[\"text\"] is an accessibility tree of the current page\n        response = client.messages.create(\n            model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n            max_tokens=512,\n            messages=[{\n                \"role\": \"user\",\n                \"content\": (\n                    f\"Task: {info['task_string']}\\n\\n\"\n                    f\"Current page:\\n{obs['text'][:3000]}\\n\\n\"\n                    \"What action do you take? Reply with a single BrowserGym action.\"\n                ),\n            }],\n        )\n        action_str = response.content[0].text.strip()\n        obs, reward, done, _, info = env.step(action_str)\n        steps += 1\n\n    env.close()\n    return {\n        \"task_id\": task_id,\n        \"success\": reward == 1.0,\n        \"steps\": steps,\n        \"task\": info.get(\"task_string\", \"\"),\n    }\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Primary metric:"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " task success rate (%). A task succeeds only if the final state of the web application exactly matches the expected state \u2014 partial credit is not awarded."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Key challenge:"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " tasks require long action sequences (average ~12 steps); early mistakes propagate and cannot be undone within an episode."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Reproducibility:"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " the web apps run in Docker containers and are reset between tasks, so results are deterministic given a fixed model."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "GAIA"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "GAIA (General AI Assistants benchmark) tests whether an agent can answer real-world questions that require tool use, multi-step reasoning, and reading non-text artifacts such as PDFs and images. Tasks are stratified across three difficulty levels: Level 1 requires one tool call, Level 2 requires several, and Level 3 requires complex multi-modal reasoning that stumps most current systems."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import json\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n# GAIA dataset is on HuggingFace: gaia-benchmark/GAIA\n# After downloading, tasks look like:\n# {\"task_id\": \"...\", \"Question\": \"...\", \"Level\": 1, \"Final answer\": \"42\"}\n\ndef answer_gaia_question(question: str, level: int, client) -> str:\n    tools = [\n        {\n            \"name\": \"web_search\",\n            \"description\": \"Search the web for information\",\n            \"input_schema\": {\n                \"type\": \"object\",\n                \"properties\": {\"query\": {\"type\": \"string\"}},\n                \"required\": [\"query\"],\n            },\n        },\n        {\n            \"name\": \"calculator\",\n            \"description\": \"Evaluate a mathematical expression\",\n            \"input_schema\": {\n                \"type\": \"object\",\n                \"properties\": {\"expression\": {\"type\": \"string\"}},\n                \"required\": [\"expression\"],\n            },\n        },\n    ]\n    messages = [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": question}]\n\n    for _ in range(20):  # L3 questions can need many steps\n        response = client.messages.create(\n            model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n            max_tokens=1024,\n            tools=tools,\n            messages=messages,\n        )\n        if response.stop_reason == \"end_turn\":\n            return next(\n                (b.text for b in response.content if hasattr(b, \"text\")), \"\"\n            )\n        # handle tool calls ...\n        break\n    return \"\"\n\n\ndef score_gaia(predicted: str, expected: str) -> bool:\n    # GAIA uses exact string match after normalisation\n    pred = predicted.strip().lower().rstrip(\".\")\n    exp = expected.strip().lower().rstrip(\".\")\n    return pred == exp\n\n\ndef evaluate_gaia_split(tasks: list, client) -> dict:\n    results = {1: [], 2: [], 3: []}\n    for task in tasks:\n        answer = answer_gaia_question(task[\"Question\"], task[\"Level\"], client)\n        correct = score_gaia(answer, task[\"Final answer\"])\n        results[task[\"Level\"]].append(correct)\n\n    return {\n        f\"L{lvl}_accuracy\": sum(v) / len(v) if v else 0.0\n        for lvl, v in results.items()\n    }\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
